    ('BUS-G 350', 'BUSINESS ECONOMETRICS', '9913', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'HH 3055', 'Haizhen Lin', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The objective of the course is to understand various econometric, statistical, and forecasting tools for making informed business decisions. Econometric theories will be studied and applied using real-world data. Topics include linear regression, logit, probit, simultaneous equations models, two-stage least squares, time series and panel data methods.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 350', 'BUSINESS ECONOMETRICS', '12038', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'HH 3055', 'Tulio Salvio Dias De Sousa', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The objective of the course is to understand various econometric, statistical, and forecasting tools for making informed business decisions. Econometric theories will be studied and applied using real-world data. Topics include linear regression, logit, probit, simultaneous equations models, two-stage least squares, time series and panel data methods.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 400', 'CAPSTONE IN ECONOMIC CONSULTING', '4566', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'CG 3044', 'Thomas Youle', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This workshop intends to develop or sharpen those skills that are associated with a successful consultant. Students taking this course are expected to be highly motivated and have basic diagnostic, analytical, and communication skills.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 455', 'TOPICS IN BUSINESS ECONOMICS AND PUBLIC POLICY', '14181', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'HH 4006', 'R. Butters', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Variable topic, variable credit course in Business Economics and Public Policy. The purpose of this course number is to provide a course number for an experimental course. The specific variable title is only expected to be used for one term.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 456', 'STRATEGY BEYOND MARKETS', '5155', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'HH 3055', 'John Maxwell', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Firms traditionally focus on outcomes: product quality, delivery time, cost and pricing. Less attention is given to process: environmental impacts, worker conditions and governance, leading to non-market risks (boycotts and negative information campaigns). Non-market risk consulting is aimed at spotting, mitigating, or eliminating these risks to drive log-run business value.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 456', 'STRATEGY BEYOND MARKETS', '6239', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 3:55 PM–5:10 PM', 'HH 3055', 'John Maxwell', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Firms traditionally focus on outcomes: product quality, delivery time, cost and pricing. Less attention is given to process: environmental impacts, worker conditions and governance, leading to non-market risks (boycotts and negative information campaigns). Non-market risk consulting is aimed at spotting, mitigating, or eliminating these risks to drive log-run business value.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 492', 'PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS FOR BUSINESS STRATEGY', '4337', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 8:00 AM–9:15 AM', 'HH 1038', 'Mohaddeseh Heydari Nejad', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course develops the analytical tools and hands-on experience with data and economic models to optimally utilize information in decision-making. In addition, students will learn: presentation and communication skills for quantitative findings, targeted programming skills in VBA, and the basics of identification for econometric models.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 492', 'PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS FOR BUSINESS STRATEGY', '6531', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'HH 1038', 'Ramses Armendariz Buaun', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course develops the analytical tools and hands-on experience with data and economic models to optimally utilize information in decision-making. In addition, students will learn: presentation and communication skills for quantitative findings, targeted programming skills in VBA, and the basics of identification for econometric models.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 492', 'PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS FOR BUSINESS STRATEGY', '12039', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'HH 1038', 'Ramses Armendariz Buaun', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course develops the analytical tools and hands-on experience with data and economic models to optimally utilize information in decision-making. In addition, students will learn: presentation and communication skills for quantitative findings, targeted programming skills in VBA, and the basics of identification for econometric models.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 540', 'MANAGERIAL ECONOMICS', '5873', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 1:00 PM–2:15 PM', 'CG 1040', 'Vikram Ahuja', 6, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The course focuses on concepts, tools, and applications of managerial economies of special importance and interest to accountants. Concepts include PVA, demand and consumer behavior, economic versus accounting cost concepts, economic value analysis, contribution margin, strategic decision analysis, marketing analysis, pricing strategies, and the role of government in economic markets.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 540', 'MANAGERIAL ECONOMICS', '30037', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:00 AM–12:15 PM', 'CG 1008', 'Vikram Ahuja', 4, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The course focuses on concepts, tools, and applications of managerial economies of special importance and interest to accountants. Concepts include PVA, demand and consumer behavior, economic versus accounting cost concepts, economic value analysis, contribution margin, strategic decision analysis, marketing analysis, pricing strategies, and the role of government in economic markets.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 570', 'THINKING STRATEGICALLY: GAME THEORY AND BUSINESS STRATEGY', '5874', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:00 AM–12:15 PM', 'CG 1008', 'Vikram Ahuja', 4, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Uses key insights from the theory of games to sharpen students'' thinking about competitive situations. Topics covered include resolving the "Prisoners'' Dilemna," deciding how much information to reveal, making credible commitments, the value of being unpredictable, creating the right reputation, and deciding when to be aggressive and when to be cooperative. Emphasis is on developing intuition rather than technique.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 570', 'THINKING STRATEGICALLY: GAME THEORY AND BUSINESS STRATEGY', '30038', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 1:00 PM–2:15 PM', 'CG 1040', 'Vikram Ahuja', 6, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Uses key insights from the theory of games to sharpen students'' thinking about competitive situations. Topics covered include resolving the "Prisoners'' Dilemna," deciding how much information to reveal, making credible commitments, the value of being unpredictable, creating the right reputation, and deciding when to be aggressive and when to be cooperative. Emphasis is on developing intuition rather than technique.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 651', 'ECONOMETRIC METHODS IN BUSINESS I', '5288', 'Class Status', 'Tu Tuesday 8:00 AM–11:00 AM', 'CG 1004', 'R. Butters', 14, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Multiple regression models, generalized least squares, and distributed lag models. Discusses various models, estimations, and inference problems. Use of a computer and application to economics and business problems.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 751', 'GAME THEORY', '14184', 'Class Status', 'W Wednesday 4:00 PM–7:00 PM', 'CG 1014', 'Marilyn Pease', 9, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Game Theory is the study of multi-person decision problems in which players consider that their actions affect each other. This course provides an introduction to graduate level game theory. Throughout the course we use applications from different business fields.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 752', 'INFORMATION ECONOMICS', '14183', 'Class Status', 'W Wednesday 4:00 PM–7:00 PM', 'CG 1014', 'Marilyn Pease', 14, NULL, 'Seminar', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Asymmetric information is a fundamental problem in almost all business transactions, from uncertainty over the quality of a product or the value of a firm, to doubts over the intentions or capabilities of a business partner. This course uses game theory to analyze how individuals and firms credibly convey information.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-G 901', 'ADVANCED RESEARCH', '1148', 'Class Status', NULL, NULL, 'Noah Stoffman', 15, NULL, 'Research', '6', NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Available to graduate students who have completed all course requirements for their doctorates, have passed doctoral qualifying examinations, and have the requisite number of degree credit hours, this course provides the advanced research students with a forum for sharing ideas and problems under the supervision of a senior researcher.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-I 304', 'HONORS I-CORE DISCUSSION', '3586', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Rachel Landis', 0, NULL, 'Discussion', '2', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-I 304', 'HONORS I-CORE DISCUSSION', '3587', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Nancy Evans', 0, NULL, 'Discussion', '2', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-I 304', 'HONORS I-CORE DISCUSSION', '3588', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Rachel Landis', 0, NULL, 'Discussion', '2', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-I 304', 'HONORS I-CORE DISCUSSION', '11948', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Rachel Landis', 0, NULL, 'Discussion', '2', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-I 304', 'HONORS I-CORE DISCUSSION', '11949', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Nancy Evans', 0, NULL, 'Discussion', '2', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-I 304', 'HONORS I-CORE DISCUSSION', '11950', 'Closed', NULL, 'WB WEB', 'Nancy Evans', 0, NULL, 'Discussion', '2', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL, ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-J 285', 'COMPETITIVE STRATEGY & INDUSTRY', '33934', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 8:00 AM–9:15 AM', 'HH 3057', 'Matthew Josefy', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Students will study a handful of distinctive industries, such that they can compare and contrast various facets of how competition plays out according to specific industries'' features. Students will utilize common frameworks and tools to assess key distinguishing features of an industry and how it compares to other industries.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-J 285', 'COMPETITIVE STRATEGY & INDUSTRY', '33935', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'HH 3057', 'Matthew Josefy', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Students will study a handful of distinctive industries, such that they can compare and contrast various facets of how competition plays out according to specific industries'' features. Students will utilize common frameworks and tools to assess key distinguishing features of an industry and how it compares to other industries.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-J 285', 'COMPETITIVE STRATEGY & INDUSTRY', '33937', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'HH 3057', 'Matthew Josefy', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Students will study a handful of distinctive industries, such that they can compare and contrast various facets of how competition plays out according to specific industries'' features. Students will utilize common frameworks and tools to assess key distinguishing features of an industry and how it compares to other industries.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-J 304', 'HONORS STRATEGIC MANAGEMENT', '1149', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:20 AM–12:35 PM', 'HH 4000', 'Angie Fairchild', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course is designed to provide an appreciation for the total firm perspective and the means by which firms create and susstain competitive advantage in today''s increasingly challenging complex business environment (domestic and global). Strategic management of a firm involves diagnosing the firm''s current situation and developing realistic solutions to strategic and organizational problems which confront top managers.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-J 304', 'HONORS STRATEGIC MANAGEMENT', '1150', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 3:45 PM–5:00 PM', 'HH 4000', 'Farhan Iqbal', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course is designed to provide an appreciation for the total firm perspective and the means by which firms create and susstain competitive advantage in today''s increasingly challenging complex business environment (domestic and global). Strategic management of a firm involves diagnosing the firm''s current situation and developing realistic solutions to strategic and organizational problems which confront top managers.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
